						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Madhuvanēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 16: 987 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The <hi rend="italic">mūlaparuḍi-pperumakkaḷ</hi> of Tirukkarugāvūr sold 3 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> and 1 <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> as tax-free land to God Mahādēva of the above village (Tirukkarugāvūr) for thirty-one <hi rend="italic">kāśu.</hi> It is also mentioned that the land which was a tax-free land earlier (in the third regnal year of Parakēsarivarman ie Uttamachōḷa ?) was now made perpetually tax-free.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. III No. 123.</p>						

						</summary>
